Extends OutlineMode and OutlineMinorMode with the command <code>outline-cycle</code> -- a single command to toggle hiding/showing.

Available at [[outline-magic.el]] (or from [http://melpa.milkbox.net/ Melpa] if you're using Emacs 24).

After installing it into a location on your <code>load-path</code>, enable it with:

<pre>
(eval-after-load 'outline
  '(progn
    (require 'outline-magic)
    (define-key outline-minor-mode-map (kbd "<C-tab>") 'outline-cycle)))
</pre>
